    "narrative": "For April 11, 2026, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** stands as our premier offensive anchor. His score of 84.88 is head and shoulders above the field, bolstered by a soft matchup against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez. The combination of an elite batting order spot (#3) and a favorable SP xERA of 4.78 provides the highest floor and ceiling on the roster. Meanwhile, **Lawrence Butler** earns the second-highest projected efficiency (74.61) despite facing Kodai Senga; his lead-off role combined with a significant 13% boost from platoon dynamics makes him a primary catalyst for runs and, crucially, stolen base opportunities today. \n\nStrategic park factors and delivery speeds are central to today\u2019s lineup construction. **Luis Arraez** and **Matt Chapman** benefit significantly from a 16% park-factor surge against Chris Bassitt, keeping their scores comfortably in the \"Strong\" range despite the tougher pitcher. We are aggressively chasing steals where possible, as evidenced by the inclusion of **Tyler Freeman** and **Bryson Stott**. Both benefit from facing pitchers with slower deliveries, with **Bryson Stott** gaining a specific 4% boost due to Pfaadt\u2019s vulnerability to the stolen base. **Daulton Varsho** remains our most marginal start at 52.92; his inclusion is purely a necessity to preserve cap space, as he faces a stiff challenge against Ryan, whose 3.32 xERA severely caps his offensive output.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision was bypassing **Wenceel Perez** (51.95), who narrowly missed the cut. While he offered potential value against Junk, the optimizer prioritized the higher efficiency scores of **Gavin Sheets** and **Jung Hoo Lee**, who both enjoy more favorable platoon matchups. Risk management remains a priority: the \"Lineup Pending\" status for most of our roster creates significant variance. Should official lineups shift **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, or **Lawrence Butler** out of their anticipated high-leverage spots, we will be forced to reconsider their daily output. Keep a close eye on weather and last-minute tactical adjustments for any further lineup oscillations.",
